indicator.description:
1. Availability  of climate risk management (CRM) in existing  disaster risk reduction (DRR) policies and plans;
2. Level of support of national agencies in improving data collection, analysis, distribution with regard to climate change;
3. Number of pilot projects for most vulnerable rural communities.

baseline.comment:
1. Lack of climate risk management (CRM) in existing  disaster risk reduction (DRR) policies and plans (2013);  
2. Limited capacity in national agencies in data processing, analysis and sharing with regard to natural and climate risks (2013);
3. Limited knowledge on appropriateness of the coping and adaptive mechanisms employed by the vulnerable rural communities (2013).
